autolisp-test harness: matrix/recap/sexp-report fail with
"FOREACH list argument must evaluate to a proper list, got T".

Observed during the Phase-4 conformance run (commit
<to be filled in by the Phase-4 commit>) and confirmed against
the pre-Phase-4 baseline (658 tests on master): the post-run
aggregation steps abort with

    [autolisp-test] matrix raised: FOREACH list argument must evaluate to a proper list, got T.
    [autolisp-test] write-sexp-report raised: FOREACH list argument must evaluate to a proper list, got T.
    [autolisp-test] print-recap raised: LENGTH expects a proper list, got T.

The test bodies themselves still execute -- `[autolisp-test]
running NNN tests on clautolisp 0.x` is printed before the
matrix step -- but the on-disk report.sexp ends up empty
(0 bytes) and the human-readable recap never lands on stdout.

Reproduction
------------

    cd autolisp-test
    make test-asdf-sbcl 2>&1 | grep -E 'matrix|recap|raised|running'

Expected: a non-zero number of passes / fails / skips.

Actual:

    [autolisp-test] running 3905 tests on clautolisp 0.x
    [autolisp-test] matrix raised: FOREACH list argument must evaluate to a proper list, got T.
    [autolisp-test] write-sexp-report raised: FOREACH list argument must evaluate to a proper list, got T.
    [autolisp-test] print-recap raised: LENGTH expects a proper list, got T.

Hypothesis
----------

One of the matrix-building paths in
autolisp-test/harness/profiles.lsp:67ff
ends up calling ~foreach~ with a non-list. Candidate sites:

  - profiles.lsp:93 `(foreach tag (cdr (assoc 'runtimes descriptor)))`
    -- if some descriptor build path stored T (not a list)
    against the `'runtimes` key, `(cdr 'T)` is invalid in
    AutoLISP.
  - profiles.lsp:39 `(foreach entry entries)` -- but `entries`
    is `*autolisp-tests*` which is a proper list.
  - profiles.lsp:25, 43 `(foreach r results)` -- `results` is
    the return value of autolisp-test-run-many, which builds
    `acc` as a list and returns `(reverse acc)`.

The fact that LENGTH gives the same complaint in
print-recap (~harness/report.lsp:251~) suggests the upstream
~matrix~ value passed into print-recap is itself T (because
the guarded matrix step returned the catcher's error sentinel
rather than nil).

Scope
-----

This is a harness bug, not a Phase-4 regression: the same error
fires on a stripped-down loader that contains only the original
658 baseline tests. Phase-4 adds ~3247 new tests on top of that
baseline; all of them run, but none of them appear in the (empty)
report file.

Acceptance
----------

- ~make test-asdf-sbcl~ emits a non-zero summary line covering
  every entry in *autolisp-test-files*.
- The on-disk ~report.sexp~ is non-empty and parses as a single
  CL form.
- ~print-recap~ no longer raises.
- A regression test for the matrix function with an empty
  ~runtimes~ list lands alongside the fix.

Resolution (2026-07-24) — DUPLICATE of autolisp-test-recap-crash-got-t
---------------------------------------------------------------------

Same bug, fixed on branch fix-test-recap-crash; see
issues/closed/autolisp-test-recap-crash-got-t.issue for the full root
cause and fix. Summary: harness bug in platform-detect.lsp — AutoLISP
`or' returns T/nil not a value, so the IMPL-NAME fallback became T and
cascaded into the matrix/recap "got T" crash; clautolisp was also
mis-detected as `unknown'. Both acceptance criteria here (non-zero
summary via `make test-asdf-sbcl'; non-empty parseable report.sexp;
print-recap no longer raises; a regression test for the matrix on an
empty runtimes list — harness/self-test.lsp) are met.
